newsitem.title: UK: Med oil products - light ends soft, others firm.
newsitem.headline: Med oil products - light ends soft, others firm.

text.p: Gasoline appeared a little more resistant to weakness in the energy complex amid good demand for product.
A refiner was heard looking for a 26,000 tonne cargo containing 95 RON unleaded gasoline, 18,000 tonnes of which contained three percent benzene, and the rest low benzene.
The same refiner was looking for a mixed leaded/unleaded cargo for Genoa.
Naphtha prices fell with crude. Offers of Skikda material were heard at around $5 over cif quotes.
Gas oil was steady to slightly stronger.
Traders said low sulphur material was fairly tight, with a few Italian players slightly short as the introduction of EN590 regulations on October 1 approaches.
Low sulphur cargoes were reported offered at quotes cif high +$5.0, basis Genoa.
Traders said 0.2 percent material was well supported by demand out of Greece and Turkey as well as a lack of Russian cargoes. Premiums on Russian material were put at quotes cif high +$2.50 to +$3.
Weaker crude futures failed to undermine fuel oil prices in the Med, essentially because of tight supplies.
Tight supplies of good quality high sulphur fuel oil together with Portugal's tender to buy up to 150,000 tonnes of fuel in September, October and November nudged prices $1 up to $107-109 fob.

Demand into Romania was still seen. A high viscosity cargo was done on Wednesday at high fob +$1.20. An Italian refinery was looking for a mid October cargo, bidding around the flat mean fob quote and being met by offers of high fob +$1.
Straight run supplies out of Russia remain tight with cargoes able to hold prices.
